00:56:32.682 --> 00:56:38.396
Or you will find yourself in a real
Mexican hell. No mariachi, no tequila...

486
00:56:38.480 --> 00:56:40.565
and no Pita.

487
00:57:19.771 --> 00:57:20.814
Crease?

488
00:57:22.899 --> 00:57:23.942
Crease.

489
00:57:26.820 --> 00:57:30.573
When I heard it was this hospital,
I was so pleased.

490
00:57:30.657 --> 00:57:34.244
There is a pastry shop nearby.
Delgado's.

491
00:57:34.327 --> 00:57:38.540
They have the best pastries in Mexico.

492
00:57:38.623 --> 00:57:42.585
Miguel Manzano. Director of the AFI.

493
00:57:42.669 --> 00:57:48.800
And a former director of Interpol, in Rome.

494
00:57:49.926 --> 00:57:51.553
- And you are?
- A friend of his.

495
00:57:53.388 --> 00:57:55.223
Rayburn.

496
00:58:10.697 --> 00:58:13.408
Do you love your daughter, señor Ramos?

497
00:58:13.491 --> 00:58:15.618
Yes. Yes.

498
00:58:15.702 --> 00:58:18.913
- Do you want to see her again?
- Yes, I do.

499
00:58:18.997 --> 00:58:20.331
Señor...

500
00:58:21.332 --> 00:58:26.254
If your daughter's life is
as important to you as it is to me,

501
00:58:26.337 --> 00:58:28.673
you will do as I say.

502
00:58:28.756 --> 00:58:30.800
Yes?

503
00:58:30.884 --> 00:58:32.427
OK, yes.

504
00:58:33.094 --> 00:58:35.221
Crease. You hear me?

505
00:58:38.725 --> 00:58:40.977
You got four of 'em, all dead.

506
00:58:42.770 --> 00:58:45.857
- Pita?
- It's...

507
00:58:47.734 --> 00:58:50.361
It's been two days.

508
00:58:50.445 --> 00:58:53.281
They're negotiating a ransom.

509
00:58:54.741 --> 00:58:58.369
These things take time, Mr Creasy.

510
00:59:02.957 --> 00:59:04.584
Crease.

511
00:59:06.794 --> 00:59:09.714
Don't fuck with me, all right?

512
00:59:15.261 --> 00:59:18.681
You have the ten million?
Do you have the money?

513
00:59:18.765 --> 00:59:22.560
- Yes, we have the money.
- Now, if you do as I say,

514
00:59:22.644 --> 00:59:27.023
the girl will be returned
exactly as she was taken.

515
00:59:27.106 --> 00:59:31.236
But if you deviate
from the process in any way...

516
00:59:31.819 --> 00:59:33.821
By the Virgin of Guadeloupe,

517
00:59:33.905 --> 00:59:36.407
I swear you will never see her again.

518
00:59:36.491 --> 00:59:39.619
I understand. Listen, I too
worship la Virgen de Guadalupe...

519
00:59:39.702 --> 00:59:41.746
I ask if you understand.

520
00:59:44.582 --> 00:59:47.835
Hello, sir.
This is Mr Ramos's attorney.

521
00:59:47.919 --> 00:59:50.880
He's going through a very difficult time,
but he understands.

522
00:59:50.964 --> 00:59:54.342
Do you understand?
Repeat the drop instructions.

523
00:59:54.425 --> 00:59:59.597
OK, the money, ten million US, will be divided
into two 15-gallon black canvas bags,

524
00:59:59.681 --> 01:00:04.018
each containing five million, which
will be checked at the bank by the KR agent,

525
01:00:04.102 --> 01:00:08.731
then driven to the house in an armoured car,
where it will be transferred to the delivery car.

526
01:00:09.565 --> 01:00:12.360
You got a flat tyre here.

527
01:00:12.443 --> 01:00:14.529
This is for you.

528
01:00:15.613 --> 01:00:17.991
Hello. Yeah.

529
01:00:18.074 --> 01:00:20.660
Listen, I need a driver to drive Samuel.

530
01:00:20.743 --> 01:00:22.996
No. Why?

531
01:00:23.079 --> 01:00:26.916
He's got a bad ticker.
He's got a heart condition.

532
01:00:27.000 --> 01:00:30.211
Look, he's a nervous kid.
He doesn't respond well to stress.

533
01:00:32.338 --> 01:00:37.010
All right, but the car will not be powerful.

534
01:00:37.093 --> 01:00:38.386
Remove the trunk lid.

535
01:00:38.720 --> 01:00:42.181
Use the maid's Valiant Acapulco.

536
01:00:42.932 --> 01:00:46.769
You will arrive at La Diana fountain at 1 a.m.

537
01:00:46.853 --> 01:00:51.024
You will drive around the circle two times.

538
01:00:51.107 --> 01:00:59.073
Samuel will remove his shirt
and hold it out the window to ID the car.

539
01:01:00.158 --> 01:01:03.911
There is a payphone on the southeast corner.

540
01:01:03.995 --> 01:01:09.834
The phone will ring.
You will answer and wait for instructions.

541
01:01:09.917 --> 01:01:14.839
There is a map on the top
of the phone. Follow it.

542
01:01:22.764 --> 01:01:25.767
- What are you doing? He said no phones.
- Relax, relax.

543
01:01:25.850 --> 01:01:29.687
I'm just trying to protect your daughter, OK?

544
01:01:34.609 --> 01:01:35.777
What's goin' on?

545
01:01:36.110 --> 01:01:38.946
Hospitals can be very dangerous places,

546
01:01:39.030 --> 01:01:42.992
especially when you have
killed two corrupt cops.

547
01:01:55.380 --> 01:01:59.342
Leave the money in the trunk of the white car

548
01:01:59.425 --> 01:02:01.511
and return to your car.

549
01:02:03.304 --> 01:02:06.641
Do not look back.

550
01:02:15.483 --> 01:02:17.151
What's going on, guys?

551
01:02:17.235 --> 01:02:18.820
Ambush!

552
01:02:24.909 --> 01:02:28.746
Remember, I'm a professional.

553
01:02:29.038 --> 01:02:36.671
If you keep your word, I will keep mine.

554
01:02:46.013 --> 01:02:48.182
- Hello?
- Mr Ramos.

555
01:02:48.266 --> 01:02:51.811
You betrayed me. You killed my nephew.

556
01:02:52.437 --> 01:02:54.063
You took my money.

557
01:02:54.147 --> 01:02:56.149
Señor Ramos...

558
01:02:56.315 --> 01:02:59.193
God be with your child.

559
01:03:01.112 --> 01:03:05.992
All right. Get outta here, all of you.
Get the fuck out of my house!

560
01:03:06.075 --> 01:03:08.369
OK, this is Lisa...

561
01:03:09.245 --> 01:03:12.039
Martin Ramos. I'm Pita's mother.

562
01:03:13.541 --> 01:03:18.421
And I'm very sorry for whatever happened
to your nephew, but I beg you...

563
01:03:18.504 --> 01:03:21.591
Please don't harm my daughter.

564
01:03:23.301 --> 01:03:26.179
This conversation is not being recorded.

565
01:03:26.262 --> 01:03:28.639
You're negotiating directly with me.

566
01:03:28.723 --> 01:03:34.353
I'm sorry. I'm really sorry.
I wish we had talked sooner, señora.

567
01:03:34.437 --> 01:03:37.148
I'm really sorry.

568
01:03:37.857 --> 01:03:39.942
Now it is too late.

569
01:03:49.660 --> 01:03:54.248
Fuck off! Get the fuck out
of my fucking house! Now!

570
01:03:55.291 --> 01:03:58.044
Get out! Get out!

571
01:04:46.342 --> 01:04:49.303
Hey, Ray. How are you...?

572
01:04:51.639 --> 01:04:55.434
- Where am I?
- Well, it looks like a dog hospital.

573
01:04:59.772 --> 01:05:03.317
Manzano was afraid
the cops were gonna kill ya.

574
01:05:04.360 --> 01:05:06.445
How you doin', doc?

575
01:05:11.492 --> 01:05:13.578
What's the matter?

576
01:05:16.789 --> 01:05:19.083
She's dead, Crease.

577
01:05:21.419 --> 01:05:26.132
It's a mess. Somebody
hijacked the drop and...

578
01:05:29.969 --> 01:05:34.473
The kidnapper's nephew was killed,
so he killed Pita.

579
01:05:46.902 --> 01:05:50.531
He has gunshot wounds
to the chest and the abdomen.

580
01:05:50.906 --> 01:05:52.908
He has a collapsed lung
which we've re-inflated.

581
01:05:52.992 --> 01:05:57.204
He's lucky to be alive.
If he doesn't rest, he will die.

582
01:05:59.957 --> 01:06:01.542
How long will he be hospitalised?

583
01:06:01.626 --> 01:06:03.544
Approximately a month.

584
01:06:06.047 --> 01:06:07.965
No.

585
01:06:15.806 --> 01:06:17.683
No.

586
01:06:22.730 --> 01:06:25.941
Did you recognise any of these men?

587
01:06:27.151 --> 01:06:31.697
No. Does that make me a suspect?

588
01:06:32.448 --> 01:06:34.408
No.

589
01:06:34.492 --> 01:06:36.577
It would be convenient, but no.

590
01:06:37.870 --> 01:06:41.957
Maybe you should show me pictures of some
Mexican cops. Maybe we'll get somewhere.

591
01:06:42.041 --> 01:06:44.460
Those were all policemen.

592
01:06:44.543 --> 01:06:47.630
Bad Judicial cops,

593
01:06:47.713 --> 01:06:52.051
protected, by a brotherhood.

594
01:06:52.134 --> 01:06:54.053
A brotherhood?

595
01:06:55.638 --> 01:06:59.392
A brotherhood, called...

596
01:07:15.366 --> 01:07:17.993
You all set?

597
01:07:18.077 --> 01:07:19.745
- Right arm.
- Yeah.

598
01:07:22.832 --> 01:07:25.334
- You OK?
- Yeah, I'm all right.

599
01:07:25.418 --> 01:07:27.545
Let's go.

600
01:08:04.206 --> 01:08:06.375
- Somebody's on us.
- Yeah.

601
01:08:07.334 --> 01:08:09.003
Lois Lane.

602
01:08:09.754 --> 01:08:13.007
Mariana something, works for Reforma.

603
01:08:13.632 --> 01:08:16.343
Newspaper journalist.

604
01:08:16.427 --> 01:08:19.680
I guess she thinks you're a scoop.

605
01:08:21.390 --> 01:08:23.017
I'll get you up to the border.

606
01:08:23.100 --> 01:08:26.562
A friend will take you to San Diego,
drop you at the Naval Hospital.

607
01:08:26.645 --> 01:08:29.064
I'm not goin', Ray.

608
01:08:29.148 --> 01:08:31.650
What are you gonna do?

609
01:08:31.734 --> 01:08:35.404
Let's take a ride by the crime scene.
She can follow us.

610
01:09:46.600 --> 01:09:48.936
Mr Creasy?

611
01:09:49.019 --> 01:09:51.772
A lot of people are looking for you.

612
01:09:52.857 --> 01:09:55.442
I'm Mariana García Guerrero.

613
01:09:56.277 --> 01:09:58.737
Reporter, for Reforma.

614
01:10:01.407 --> 01:10:03.784
Nice to meet you.

615
01:10:03.868 --> 01:10:05.828
I found this across the street.

616
01:10:09.498 --> 01:10:11.125
Open it.

617
01:10:14.795 --> 01:10:17.506
It's Santa Muerte. Death worship.

618
01:10:21.468 --> 01:10:25.014
- They've put a curse on you.
- A little late.

619
01:10:29.018 --> 01:10:33.355
- What are you going to do?
- I'm gonna get in my truck and leave.

620
01:10:36.525 --> 01:10:38.903
I can help you.

621
01:10:40.779 --> 01:10:44.992
There's a brotherhood called La Hermandad.

622
01:10:45.075 --> 01:10:48.954
It protects government officials,
corrupt police and organised crime

623
01:10:49.038 --> 01:10:53.542
at a level that is too difficult
for me to reach.

624
01:10:53.626 --> 01:10:55.169
OK.

625
01:10:55.252 --> 01:11:00.966
And I think that you and Lupita Ramos
are victims of this organisation.

626
01:11:01.050 --> 01:11:07.598
I want to expose them. Talk to me, give me
your story, and then I can help you. Please.

627
01:11:12.144 --> 01:11:14.438
Help me do what?

628
01:11:15.397 --> 01:11:18.525
You're gonna help me do what?

629
01:11:19.360 --> 01:11:22.905
- You're a stranger here, no?
- That's right.

630
01:11:22.988 --> 01:11:27.368
You're going to need friends
that know their way around.

631
01:11:27.451 --> 01:11:29.536
OK.

632
01:11:29.620 --> 01:11:32.164
OK, friend that's gonna help me.

633
01:11:34.541 --> 01:11:36.669
Pleasure to meet you.

634
01:11:36.752 --> 01:11:41.215
Tell your driver to keep his distance
next time. All right, friend?

635
01:12:03.028 --> 01:12:07.491
- You'll be Stateside by supper time.
- I'm gonna need some help first, though.

636
01:12:07.574 --> 01:12:10.661
You don't stop bleeding,
you won't last a day in your shape.

637
01:12:10.744 --> 01:12:14.873
- Is that a yes or is that a no?
- Yeah! But...

638
01:12:14.957 --> 01:12:17.084
- I'm done killing. I told you that.
- OK.

639
01:12:17.167 --> 01:12:19.128
Anything else is yours.

640
01:12:25.551 --> 01:12:30.139
- You're talkin' about war, Crease.
- Exactly. Can you help me?

641
01:12:33.017 --> 01:12:34.893
- Yeah.
- Good.

642
01:13:49.760 --> 01:13:51.845
Creasy?

643
01:14:46.275 --> 01:14:48.861
What are you doin' here?

644
01:14:56.368 --> 01:14:58.787
I came to get my stuff.

645
01:14:58.871 --> 01:15:02.332
Couldn't find my Bible.
I thought it might be in here.

646
01:15:02.416 --> 01:15:05.961
- I borrowed it.
- OK.

647
01:15:07.462 --> 01:15:09.423
It's crazy, huh?

648
01:15:10.340 --> 01:15:14.887
One week we're figuring out which
nightclub to go to, and the next thing I'm...

649
01:15:14.970 --> 01:15:17.097
readin' the Bible.

650
01:15:17.181 --> 01:15:19.850
It's a good thing. You hold on to it.

651
01:15:24.396 --> 01:15:29.234
I keep thinkin' if only we hadn't...

652
01:15:32.154 --> 01:15:34.239
It's like...

653
01:15:36.366 --> 01:15:42.831
My whole life all I've ever thought about
was what I could get for myself.

654
01:15:42.915 --> 01:15:45.834
Not my own baby.

655
01:15:48.212 --> 01:15:55.802
She needed me so much, and sometimes
I felt like I had nothin' to give her.

656
01:15:55.886 --> 01:15:58.889
Just... I don't know what to do.

657
01:16:01.475 --> 01:16:05.062
- What are you gonna do?
- What I do best.

658
01:16:05.145 --> 01:16:07.231
I'm gonna kill 'em.

659
01:16:08.232 --> 01:16:14.947
Anyone that was involved, who profited
from it, anybody who opens their eyes at me.

660
01:16:15.030 --> 01:16:16.949
You kill 'em all.

661
01:17:20.178 --> 01:17:21.972
REFORMA NEWSPAPER

662
01:17:32.691 --> 01:17:34.276
Yeah, it's me.

663
01:17:34.985 --> 01:17:38.780
- Mr Creasy.
- I need the licence... No, excuse me.

664
01:17:38.864 --> 01:17:43.952
I need the name and address of someone
whose licence number is C5TK8.

665
01:17:44.036 --> 01:17:47.873
That's C5TK8.

666
01:17:47.956 --> 01:17:52.044
I got everything but the last digit,
so I need ten possible matches.

667
01:17:52.127 --> 01:17:54.463
And when do I find out
which of the ten it is?

668
01:17:54.546 --> 01:17:57.341
- Eventually.
- But where do I reach you?

669
01:17:57.424 --> 01:17:59.509
I'll call you.

670
01:18:04.890 --> 01:18:09.728
AGENCY FOR FEDERAL INVESTIGATION
MEXICO CITY

671
01:18:10.604 --> 01:18:12.147
Do you know who he is?

672
01:18:12.230 --> 01:18:15.108
Do you know what he's been doing
the last 16 years?

673
01:18:15.942 --> 01:18:17.527
Counter-insurgency work in Thailand,

674
01:18:17.611 --> 01:18:18.820
Pakistan...

675
01:18:18.904 --> 01:18:21.615
Jordan, Angola, Lebanon.
Yes, I know all of that.

676
01:18:21.698 --> 01:18:22.991
He's an assassin...

677
01:18:23.075 --> 01:18:27.287
and you want to help him identify
the owner of a car for him?

678
01:18:27.913 --> 01:18:31.249
He can go places we can't.

679
01:18:32.292 --> 01:18:35.212
If you don't want to use him... I will.

680
01:18:40.175 --> 01:18:42.469
When do I get to sleep with you again?

681
01:18:42.552 --> 01:18:44.137
We never sleep. We fuck.

682
01:18:44.221 --> 01:18:45.931
Give it to me.

683
01:18:46.932 --> 01:18:49.101
Give it to me.

684
01:19:29.683 --> 01:19:31.435
Jorge González.

685
01:19:33.019 --> 01:19:34.646
I'm a Judicial Policeman.

686
01:19:35.105 --> 01:19:38.191
Drive.

687
01:19:38.275 --> 01:19:39.693
OK.

688
01:20:05.760 --> 01:20:08.054
What are you gonna do?

689
01:20:08.138 --> 01:20:10.557
What I do best.

690
01:20:12.267 --> 01:20:16.438
Anyone that was involved, who profited
from it, anybody who opens their eyes at me.

691
01:20:16.521 --> 01:20:18.607
I'm gonna kill 'em.

692
01:21:02.275 --> 01:21:03.235
Can you hear me?

693
01:21:03.568 --> 01:21:04.694
My head hurts.

694
01:21:08.698 --> 01:21:10.492
I am going to ask questions.

695
01:21:13.036 --> 01:21:15.080
If you don't answer fully and truthfully,

696
01:21:15.163 --> 01:21:17.582
you will suffer much more than you have to.

697
01:21:18.291 --> 01:21:20.669
I'm going to cut your fingers off.

698
01:21:26.508 --> 01:21:29.219
One by one, if I have to.

699
01:21:30.262 --> 01:21:32.430
This is to stop the bleeding.

700
01:21:35.976 --> 01:21:38.311
Don't mess with me.

701
01:21:40.689 --> 01:21:43.483
You know who I am?

702
01:21:44.901 --> 01:21:47.487
A member of La Hermandad.

703
01:21:50.490 --> 01:21:52.450
Correct.

704
01:22:24.691 --> 01:22:29.946
What do you want to know?

705
01:22:30.780 --> 01:22:32.157
The Ramos kidnapping...

706
01:22:33.950 --> 01:22:37.412
What went wrong at the drop?

707
01:22:40.749 --> 01:22:43.543
We were just ordered to take her.

708
01:22:44.294 --> 01:22:46.129
That's all we did.

709
01:22:47.213 --> 01:22:48.131
Ordered by who?

710
01:22:48.465 --> 01:22:49.758
I don't know.

711
01:22:50.091 --> 01:22:52.427
You don't know?

712
01:22:59.434 --> 01:23:00.769
We work in separate groups.

713
01:23:00.852 --> 01:23:01.936
A voice calls.

714
01:23:02.020 --> 01:23:03.146
We grab the target

715
01:23:03.229 --> 01:23:06.316
and deliver it to the guardians.

716
01:23:10.111 --> 01:23:11.863
The bosses never see the target,

717
01:23:12.197 --> 01:23:13.782
they just make the deal.

718
01:23:16.117 --> 01:23:18.411
Who ordered it?

719
01:23:23.416 --> 01:23:24.501
We call him The Voice.

720
01:23:25.043 --> 01:23:26.586
The Voice. OK.

721
01:23:27.170 --> 01:23:28.338
The Voice.

722
01:23:29.714 --> 01:23:31.091
The Voice.

723
01:23:32.676 --> 01:23:34.010
The Voice. How do I find him?

724
01:23:40.433 --> 01:23:42.560
You don't know?

