- No, I don't.

985
01:53:05.530 --> 01:53:08.324
You'll never know how hard it is
to tell your wife the truth.

986
01:53:08.408 --> 01:53:11.327
No, you have a wife!
You tell me what happened!

987
01:53:11.411 --> 01:53:15.707
- It was in this room that my father...
- I don't give a fuck about your father!

988
01:53:15.790 --> 01:53:19.711
He prayed for his gambling debts
and his infidelities to be forgiven.

989
01:53:19.794 --> 01:53:21.171
- Samuel!
- What?

990
01:53:21.254 --> 01:53:26.050
- I love you! Tell me the truth!
- I didn't inherit a kingdom! That's the truth!

991
01:53:26.134 --> 01:53:29.429
You wanna know the truth?
I inherited his debt and his mess!

992
01:53:29.512 --> 01:53:32.474
- Tell me what happened to my baby!
- I inherited his lawyer!

993
01:53:32.557 --> 01:53:35.101
Say it! Say it! Say it!

994
01:53:35.185 --> 01:53:37.854
Say it! Be a fuckin' man!

995
01:53:41.441 --> 01:53:45.904
Jordan told me she'd sit in a room
and watch cartoons all day.

996
01:53:45.987 --> 01:53:48.406
And she'd eat ice cream.

997
01:53:48.490 --> 01:53:52.243
And we'd have her back in two days.
He lied to me!

998
01:53:52.327 --> 01:53:55.246
That's why he's fucking dead. I did it!

999
01:53:55.330 --> 01:53:57.415
I did it, Lisa!

1000
01:53:57.999 --> 01:54:00.210
I agreed to the kidnapping.

1001
01:54:00.293 --> 01:54:03.796
I did it for us. For the three of us.

1002
01:54:11.846 --> 01:54:13.932
I'm so sorry, Lisa.

1003
01:54:20.313 --> 01:54:22.398
You kill him.

1004
01:54:23.858 --> 01:54:25.652
You kill him, or I will.

1005
01:54:56.849 --> 01:54:59.060
You know how they say a...

1006
01:55:00.436 --> 01:55:03.523
bullet always tells the truth.

1007
01:55:12.490 --> 01:55:14.576
It never lies.

1008
01:55:27.338 --> 01:55:30.341
It didn't work for me, Samuel,

1009
01:55:30.425 --> 01:55:32.510
but maybe...

1010
01:55:35.680 --> 01:55:38.683
maybe it'll work for you.

1011
01:55:47.317 --> 01:55:48.776
I'll pray for you.

1012
01:57:25.373 --> 01:57:28.710
This is definitely the address
from the ATM card.

1013
01:57:30.294 --> 01:57:33.840
The PIN number was a great locator.

1014
01:57:33.923 --> 01:57:38.594
But there's no one that sounds
anything like The Voice.

1015
01:57:40.596 --> 01:57:43.182
Who's that?

1016
01:57:44.016 --> 01:57:45.351
He's the man.

1017
01:57:45.435 --> 01:57:46.894
The Voice.

1018
01:57:47.520 --> 01:57:49.772
My guys got into the house...

1019
01:57:51.232 --> 01:57:54.026
on the pretext of giving cholera shots.

1020
01:57:56.738 --> 01:57:59.031
We had to inject the whole barrio.

1021
01:58:01.659 --> 01:58:05.872
We bugged the house
and stole the picture of him.

1022
01:58:14.380 --> 01:58:17.425
Now it's time to pursue him.

1023
01:58:18.468 --> 01:58:21.888
We have to put his photo in
tomorrow's newspaper.

1024
01:58:57.340 --> 01:59:00.343
If you value your life,

1025
01:59:00.468 --> 01:59:03.638
you won't publish those photos.

1026
01:59:19.362 --> 01:59:22.281
- Mr Creasy?
- Yeah, it's me.

1027
01:59:22.365 --> 01:59:25.576
I traced the PIN for you
and I have an address.

1028
01:59:25.660 --> 01:59:26.452
Yeah?

1029
01:59:26.536 --> 01:59:30.039
The cardholder is Reina Rosas Sanchez,
the wife of The Voice.

1030
01:59:30.122 --> 01:59:34.418
She lives in Los Arcos,
apartment 26D, via Appia.

1031
01:59:34.502 --> 01:59:36.963
- Good.
- And another thing.

1032
01:59:37.046 --> 01:59:39.382
In today's paper is a picture of The Voice.

1033
01:59:39.465 --> 01:59:40.925
FEAR HAS A VOICE.

1034
01:59:41.008 --> 01:59:42.635
Good. Thank you.

1035
02:00:56.667 --> 02:00:57.543
He's in.

1036
02:00:57.627 --> 02:00:59.337
What do we do?

1037
02:00:59.921 --> 02:01:01.047
Nothing. Nothing.

1038
02:01:56.268 --> 02:01:57.687
Out of my house, you son of a bitch!

1039
02:01:57.770 --> 02:01:59.188
Stop there!

1040
02:02:47.653 --> 02:02:49.363
Get out. The kids out. Now!

1041
02:02:58.664 --> 02:02:59.915
Sit down.

1042
02:03:03.044 --> 02:03:04.545
Sit down!

1043
02:03:06.881 --> 02:03:08.132
Reina Rosas, yes?

1044
02:03:16.766 --> 02:03:20.019
Who is this? Who is this?

1045
02:03:34.200 --> 02:03:34.700
Daniel.

1046
02:03:34.909 --> 02:03:35.826
Daniel what?

1047
02:03:36.368 --> 02:03:37.536
Daniel Rosas Sanchez.

1048
02:03:39.455 --> 02:03:42.166
The Voice?

1049
02:03:45.795 --> 02:03:47.505
And this is his brother?

1050
02:03:51.258 --> 02:03:52.218
What is his name?

1051
02:03:55.554 --> 02:03:56.597
What is his name?

1052
02:03:57.681 --> 02:03:58.307
Aurelio.

1053
02:03:58.390 --> 02:04:01.102
Aurelio Rosas Sanchez, OK.

1054
02:04:05.689 --> 02:04:07.817
OK.

1055
02:04:14.532 --> 02:04:17.326
And you are Daniel's woman, right?

1056
02:04:19.370 --> 02:04:20.663
How do you contact him?

1057
02:04:23.415 --> 02:04:25.417
How do you contact him?

1058
02:04:25.709 --> 02:04:27.878
We page him,

1059
02:04:31.382 --> 02:04:33.259
and he calls back on his cellphone.

1060
02:04:36.011 --> 02:04:37.596
Call him.

1061
02:04:49.316 --> 02:04:51.360
There's no signal in here.

1062
02:04:51.443 --> 02:04:53.863
We have to go on the roof.

1063
02:04:56.490 --> 02:04:57.533
Let's go outside.

1064
02:05:06.709 --> 02:05:08.544
Outside.

1065
02:05:20.848 --> 02:05:22.016
They're going to get a call.

1066
02:05:23.434 --> 02:05:25.144
Be ready to track him.

1067
02:05:26.103 --> 02:05:29.732
If we're lucky he'll lead us to The Voice.

1068
02:05:51.921 --> 02:05:53.130
Hola, Daniel.

1069
02:05:53.214 --> 02:05:56.675
- Señor Creasy.
- Yeah.

1070
02:05:56.759 --> 02:05:59.261
Yeah, I got your family here.

1071
02:05:59.345 --> 02:06:02.181
Your brother doesn't look too good.

1072
02:06:02.264 --> 02:06:06.352
Yeah, Reina, she's what,
about eight months? Yeah?

1073
02:06:07.269 --> 02:06:09.855
You wanna negotiate?

1074
02:06:12.274 --> 02:06:18.697
The most important thing in life is family.
Do you agree?

1075
02:06:20.407 --> 02:06:21.784
I agree.

1076
02:06:23.494 --> 02:06:26.080
There you are, you have my family.

1077
02:06:26.163 --> 02:06:29.041
Well, most of my family.

1078
02:06:29.667 --> 02:06:33.295
My wife and I are separated.
You know how that is.

1079
02:06:33.379 --> 02:06:37.174
Now, tell me seriously,
how much do you want?

1080
02:06:41.387 --> 02:06:44.890
Your brother wants to speak to you.
Here, hold on.

1081
02:06:50.187 --> 02:06:51.438
What the hell do you want?

1082
02:06:53.023 --> 02:06:55.067
Listen to me! Listen!

1083
02:06:55.150 --> 02:06:58.279
I'll take your family apart
piece by piece. You understand me?

1084
02:06:58.362 --> 02:07:00.489
Piece by piece! Shut up!

1085
02:07:01.657 --> 02:07:04.451
I don't want your money.

1086
02:07:04.535 --> 02:07:07.413
You understand me? You understand me?

1087
02:07:07.496 --> 02:07:10.082
I want you!

1088
02:07:42.781 --> 02:07:44.658
I'm listening.

1089
02:07:44.742 --> 02:07:48.370
I'm listening, Daniel. I'm listening.

1090
02:07:54.126 --> 02:07:57.796
All right. I will give you a life for a life.

1091
02:07:59.381 --> 02:08:01.925
Whose life? What are you talkin' about?

1092
02:08:02.009 --> 02:08:04.845
Whose life, Daniel? I want you!

1093
02:08:05.471 --> 02:08:08.474
I will give you her life. For your life.

1094
02:08:08.557 --> 02:08:12.978
And in exchange, I will get my life back.

1095
02:08:13.062 --> 02:08:18.192
- What life? Whose life?
- The girl's. Pita's.

1096
02:08:20.944 --> 02:08:23.906
- Pita's dead!
- Creasy!

1097
02:08:25.074 --> 02:08:29.495
I'm a businessman.
A girl dead is worth nothing.

1098
02:08:29.578 --> 02:08:30.621
She's alive.

1099
02:08:34.708 --> 02:08:36.794
All right.

1100
02:08:38.670 --> 02:08:44.051
I want proof of life, you hear me?
I want proof of life. I want...

1101
02:08:44.134 --> 02:08:47.513
I want the name of her bear.
What does she call her bear?

1102
02:08:47.596 --> 02:08:52.184
You tell her to tell you to tell me
what she calls her bear.

1103
02:09:03.278 --> 02:09:05.239
Little one...

1104
02:09:05.322 --> 02:09:07.616
What do you call your teddy bear?

1105
02:09:21.547 --> 02:09:23.215
Yeah?

1106
02:09:23.298 --> 02:09:26.927
Creasy. She calls the bear Creasy Bear.

1107
02:09:32.224 --> 02:09:33.559
Remember...

1108
02:09:33.642 --> 02:09:35.811
I will give you her life

1109
02:09:35.894 --> 02:09:37.896
for your life

1110
02:09:38.397 --> 02:09:40.774
and the life of my brother.

1111
02:09:43.193 --> 02:09:45.279
OK.

1112
02:09:46.989 --> 02:09:48.657
OK.

1113
02:09:49.700 --> 02:09:53.662
I give you your brother, you give me the girl.

1114
02:09:53.745 --> 02:09:56.582
- All right.
- Where?

1115
02:10:11.263 --> 02:10:15.642
He left the roof. We lost the signal.

1116
02:10:15.726 --> 02:10:17.269
We got cut off.

1117
02:10:19.188 --> 02:10:21.023
We lost him. We lost him.

1118
02:10:23.317 --> 02:10:24.276
Damn.

1119
02:10:41.418 --> 02:10:44.880
- Hello?
- Lisa, listen to me. Don't hang up.

1120
02:10:44.963 --> 02:10:47.049
I think Pita's alive.

1121
02:10:48.967 --> 02:10:51.261
I can't take this any more.

1122
02:10:51.345 --> 02:10:56.225
Take the road to Puebla.
Get off junction 34, south side.

1123
02:10:56.308 --> 02:10:58.393
I'll meet you there in two hours.

1124
02:11:44.314 --> 02:11:46.650
So where is she?

1125
02:11:48.110 --> 02:11:52.489
She's right over there.
You see those two cars out there?

1126
02:11:57.786 --> 02:11:59.871
Pita's kidnapper, Daniel...

1127
02:12:01.081 --> 02:12:03.292
Here's his brother.

1128
02:12:05.168 --> 02:12:06.795
Here.

1129
02:12:07.838 --> 02:12:10.591
I'm goin' up on the bridge to get Pita.

1130
02:12:10.674 --> 02:12:14.970
Anything goes wrong, you put it to his head,

1131
02:12:15.053 --> 02:12:18.140
you pull the trigger, all right?

1132
02:12:18.223 --> 02:12:20.767
You understand?

1133
02:12:23.645 --> 02:12:28.275
You don't let him loose

1134
02:12:28.358 --> 02:12:31.153
until she's with you, you got it?

1135
02:12:34.072 --> 02:12:36.825
And you don't wait for me, OK?

1136
02:12:40.203 --> 02:12:43.373
- Yeah.
- You'll be all right. You OK?

1137
02:12:43.457 --> 02:12:44.958
Yeah.

1138
02:14:30.272 --> 02:14:32.023
Creasy!

1139
02:14:33.608 --> 02:14:35.694
Creasy!

1140
02:14:36.862 --> 02:14:39.406
Creasy!

1141
02:14:56.506 --> 02:14:58.049
- You all right?
- Yeah.

1142
02:14:58.133 --> 02:15:00.886
They didn't hurt you?

1143
02:15:02.387 --> 02:15:04.473
Hi.

1144
02:15:06.016 --> 02:15:10.353
All right, your mother's waiting for you.
She's at the end the bridge.

1145
02:15:10.437 --> 02:15:14.065
- OK, you go home.
- OK.

1146
02:15:14.149 --> 02:15:17.068
- All right.
- Where are you going?

1147
02:15:20.530 --> 02:15:22.616
I'm goin' home too.

1148
02:15:24.618 --> 02:15:26.203
I'm goin' to Blue Bayou.

1149
02:15:33.418 --> 02:15:35.504
I got something for you.

1150
02:15:38.465 --> 02:15:40.634
I got the last number too.

1151
02:15:42.010 --> 02:15:43.553
I love you, Creasy.

1152
02:15:47.098 --> 02:15:49.434
And you love me, don't you?

1153
02:15:49.518 --> 02:15:51.895
Yes, I do.

1154
02:15:51.978 --> 02:15:54.147
Now, come on, Pita, go.

1155
02:15:55.190 --> 02:15:57.275
- Go. Run.
- Bye.

1156
02:16:12.791 --> 02:16:14.125
Pita!

1157
02:16:14.209 --> 02:16:16.086
- Mom!
- Baby, come here! It's OK!

1158
02:16:16.169 --> 02:16:17.963
- Mom!
- Come on.

1159
02:16:18.046 --> 02:16:20.715
OK, I'll let you go now.

1160
02:16:20.799 --> 02:16:23.426
Mom!

1161
02:19:46.921 --> 02:19:54.637
JOHN W CREASY
JAN 4, 1956 - DEC 16, 2003

1162
02:19:54.721 --> 02:20:04.720
DEC 16, 2003

